cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning multilingual sentence embeddings and improving retrieval tasks, which are relevant to natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to learning embeddings using a dual-encoder with additive margin softmax, which involves machine learning techniques.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the embeddings on retrieval tasks, including document-level retrieval and mining tasks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach to learning embeddings that achieves state-of-the-art results on several tasks.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using a second-stage scorer to improve results, which could involve computer vision techniques.
